{"document":"=============================================\n\nAuthor: Ascendion AAVA\n\nCreated on:\n\nDescription: Oracle stored procedure for orchestrating full refresh ETL pipeline across 12 bronze layer tables with batch processing and audit logging\n\n=============================================\n\n# 1. Overview of Program\n\nThis stored procedure orchestrates a complete full-refresh ETL pipeline for the bronze layer by sequentially invoking 12 individual table load procedures, capturing execution metrics, and logging comprehensive audit information including batch tracking, row counts, execution times, and error handling for the entire pipeline execution.\n\n# 2. Code Structure and Design\n\n- Declares procedure bronze.usp_Load_bronze_Layer_Full with no input parameters\n- Declares 18 local variables for tracking execution state, timing, row counts, error details, and batch identification\n- Initializes v_BatchID using current timestamp formatted as 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS.FF3'\n- Logs pipeline start information including timestamp, executing user, and batch ID using DBMS_OUTPUT\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_New_Monthly_HC_Report procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Increments v_TablesProcessed counter after each table load\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_SchTask procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_Hiring_Initiator_Project_Info procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_Timesheet_New procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_report_392_all procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_vw_billing_timesheet_daywise_ne procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_vw_consultant_timesheet_daywise procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_DimDate procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_Mexico procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_Canada procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Invokes bronze.usp_Load_bz_holidays_India procedure with v_BatchID parameter\n- Executes SELECT query with COUNT and SUM aggregation on bronze.bz_Audit_Log table filtering by batch_id and status = 'SUCCESS'\n- Retrieves v_TablesSucceeded count and v_TotalRowsInserted sum from audit log\n- Executes SELECT query with COUNT and SUM aggregation on bronze.bz_Audit_Log table filtering by batch_id and status = 'FAILED'\n- Retrieves v_TablesFailed count and v_TotalRowsFailed sum from audit log\n- Calculates v_TotalRowsProcessed by summing v_TotalRowsInserted and v_TotalRowsFailed\n- Captures v_EndTime using SYSTIMESTAMP function\n- Calculates v_ExecutionTime in seconds using EXTRACT functions on timestamp interval\n- Logs completion summary including end time, execution time, table counts, and row counts using DBMS_OUTPUT\n- Inserts master audit record into bronze.bz_Audit_Log table with aggregated pipeline metrics\n- Executes COMMIT to persist audit log entry\n- Implements EXCEPTION handler for WHEN OTHERS condition\n- Captures error details using SQLERRM and SQLCODE functions\n- Calculates execution time in exception block\n- Sets v_OverallStatus to 'FAILED' in exception handler\n- Logs error information including error number, severity, state, line, and message using DBMS_OUTPUT\n- Inserts error audit record into bronze.bz_Audit_Log table with error details\n- Executes COMMIT in exception handler\n- Raises application error using RAISE_APPLICATION_ERROR with error code -20001\n\n# 3. Data Flow and Processing Logic\n\n```text\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| START            | -> | INITIALIZE VARS  | -> | GENERATE BATCH   | -> | LOG START        |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| LOAD TABLE 4     | <- | LOAD TABLE 3     | <- | LOAD TABLE 2     | <- | LOAD TABLE 1     |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                      |\n                      v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| LOAD TABLE 5     | -> | LOAD TABLE 6     | -> | LOAD TABLE 7     | -> | LOAD TABLE 8     |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| LOAD TABLE 12    | <- | LOAD TABLE 11    | <- | LOAD TABLE 10    | <- | LOAD TABLE 9     |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                      |\n                      v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| QUERY SUCCESS    | -> | QUERY FAILED     | -> | CALC TOTALS      | -> | CALC EXEC TIME   |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n| END              | <- | COMMIT           | <- | INSERT AUDIT     |\n+------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                                        +------------------+\n                                        | ERROR HANDLER    |\n                                        +------------------+\n                                              |\n                                              v\n                                        +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                        | CAPTURE ERROR    | -> | LOG ERROR        | -> | INSERT ERROR     |\n                                        +------------------+    +------------------+    +------------------+\n                                                                                          |\n                                                                                          v\n                                                                                    +------------------+\n                                                                                    | RAISE ERROR      |\n                                                                                    +------------------+\n```\n\n# 4. Data Mapping\n\n| Target Object Name | Target Attribute Name | Source Object Name | Source Attribute Name | Remarks |\n|--------------------|-----------------------|--------------------|-----------------------|---------|\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | source_table | Literal | 'source_layer.*' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | target_table | Literal | 'bronze.*' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | load_timestamp | Variable | v_StartTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | start_timestamp | Variable | v_StartTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | end_timestamp | Variable | v_EndTime | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | processed_by | Variable | v_CurrentUser | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | processing_time | Variable | v_ExecutionTime | Derived attribute |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | status | Variable | v_OverallStatus | Conditional logic |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_processed | Variable | v_TotalRowsProcessed | Derived attribute |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_inserted | Variable | v_TotalRowsInserted | Aggregation rule |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | records_failed | Variable | v_TotalRowsFailed | Aggregation rule |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | batch_id | Variable | v_BatchID | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | load_type | Literal | 'FULL_REFRESH_ALL_TABLES' | 1 to 1 mapping |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | created_date | Function | SYSTIMESTAMP | Function rule |\n| bronze.bz_Audit_Log | error_message | Variable | v_ErrorMessage | Conditional logic |\n\n# 5. Complexity Analysis\n\n| Category | Measurement |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Number of Transformations | 0 |\n| Number of ETL Processes | 12 |\n| Number of Target Tables / Objects | 13 |\n| Number of Source Tables / Objects | 1 |\n| Number of Data Loads | 12 |\n| Number of JOIN Operations | 0 |\n| Number of Aggregation Operations | 4 |\n| Number of Sorting Operations | 0 |\n| Number of Cursors | 0 |\n| Number of Loops | 0 |\n| Conditional Logic Blocks | 0 |\n| Error Handling Blocks | 1 |\n| Logging/Audit Mechanisms | 3 |\n| External Dependencies | 12 |\n| System Integrations | 0 |\n| Overall Complexity Score (0–100) | 45 |\n\n# 6. Sensitive and Privacy Data Assessment\n\nNo sensitive data found\n\n# 7. Key Outputs\n\n- bronze.bz_New_Monthly_HC_Report table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_SchTask table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_Hiring_Initiator_Project_Info table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_Timesheet_New table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_report_392_all table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_vw_billing_timesheet_daywise_ne table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_vw_consultant_timesheet_daywise table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_DimDate table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_holidays_Mexico table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_holidays_Canada table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_holidays table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_holidays_India table loaded via procedure call\n- bronze.bz_Audit_Log table with master pipeline execution record\n\n# 8. API Cost Calculations\n\nAPI cost for this call: 0.0000 USD"}